World of Esports is the place to catch up on the latest and best from the world of esports. From CS:GO, to League of Legends and Rocket League, EsportsCenter brings news, interviews, plays of the week and much more in this brand new show, which aims to provide exceptional insight into the world of competitive gaming. Featuring host OJ Borg.

ESL One will be hosting Poland's first ever DOTA 2 Major: Sixteen teams from across the globe will fight for a part of the $1,000,000 USD prize pool and 1,500 qualifying points for The International 2018. The playoffs will be held on February 24-25, 2018 at the Spodek Arena in Katowice, Poland. Get ready for the quarterfinal between Virtus.pro and Evil Geniuses.

North America Spring Regional Championship took place at ESL Studio, Burbank in California. Top 2 will qualify for the 2016 Heroes of the Storm Spring Global Championship, and the winning team will skip the first group stage there. See the teams compete in NA Spring Regional Championship for the prize pool of 1.000.000 dollars. This game is the semifinal between Cloud9 and Tempo Storm.

Everyones attention is to South Korea, where League of Legends players from across the globe will head to IEM Gyeonggi from December 2016, marking the first IEM tournament in the country since Season 3. The event will take place at Goyang Sports Center where eight League of Legends teams will battle for the IEM Gyeonggi championship and a spot at the IEM World Championship in Katowice, Poland in 2017. Two teams from Korea will defend their home ground in the tournament, with representatives from Europe, North America, China, LMS, and two wildcard teams rounding out the lineup.
